= Oracle 10g Express Edition Setup =
== Limitations ==
* 1GB memory (max)
* 4GB disk space (max)
* one database (max)

== install ==
[http://www.oracle.com/technology/software/products/database/xe/htdocs/102xelinsoft.html Download Oracle XE]

* download oracle-xe-10.2.0-1.0.i386.rpm
* download oracle-xe-client-10.2.1-1.0.i386.rpm

=== Letting yum resolve deps ===
nogpgcheck is required because the oracle rpms are not signed.
* sudo yum install --nogpgcheck oracle-xe-10.2.0-1.0.i386.rpm oracle-xe-client-10.2.1-1.0.i386.rpm

=== manually ===

* sudo yum install libaio
* sudo rpm -Uvh oracle-xe-10.2.0-1.0.i386.rpm oracle-xe-client-10.2.1-1.0.i386.rpm


== setup server ==
Configure the Oracle XE database


{{{
 sudo /etc/init.d/oracle-xe configure
}}}


Here are some sane values:
{{{
 HTTP port: 9000 (8080 is tomcat)
 listener port: 1521
 password:dog8code for SYS/SYSTEM
 have oracle start at boot: y
}}}

Login to the webui and configure a user:
* browse to http://127.0.0.1:9000/apex
* login: sys
* click Administration
* click Database Users
* click "Create >" button
* username: '''beacon'''
* password: '''beacon'''
* Confirm password: '''beacon'''
* Give beacon all system privileges (check All)
* click Create button


== setup client ==
You need to put the Oracle clients on your path.
{{{
 export PATH=$PATH:/usr/lib/oracle/xe/app/oracle/product/10.2.0/client/bin/
}}}

You also need to configure the tns names entry for your database:
{{{
 XE =
    (DESCRIPTION =
       (ADDRESS_LIST =
          (ADDRESS = (PROTOCOL = TCP)(HOST = localhost)(PORT = 1521))
       )
       (CONNECT_DATA =
          (SERVICE_NAME = xe)
       )
    )
}}}

== setup schema ==
{{{
 cd $SVNDIR/eng/schema
 make satellite-clean satellite-release TBS=USERS SQLUSER=beacon/beacon@xe
}}}

